<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Java Developer Projects</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f4f4f9;
            color: #333;
        }
        header {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            padding: 1rem 0;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 2rem auto;
            padding: 1rem;
            background: white;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            border-radius: 8px;
        }
        .project {
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
        }
        .project h3 {
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            color: #4CAF50;
        }
        .project p {
            margin: 0.5rem 0;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }
        footer {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 2rem;
            padding: 1rem;
            background-color: #333;
            color: white;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Java Developer Projects "${status}"</h1>
    </header>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="project">
            <h3>1. E-commerce Web Application</h3>
            <p><strong>Description:</strong> Developed an online shopping platform using Spring Boot, Hibernate, and MySQL.</p>
            <p><strong>Features:</strong> Product search, user authentication, shopping cart, and order management.</p>
            <p><strong>Technologies Used:</strong> Java, Spring Boot, Hibernate, MySQL, Thymeleaf, Bootstrap.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="project">
            <h3>2. Employee Management System</h3>
            <p><strong>Description:</strong> A system for managing employee records, including adding, updating, and viewing employee details.</p>
            <p><strong>Features:</strong> CRUD operations, department assignments, and performance tracking.</p>
            <p><strong>Technologies Used:</strong> Java, JDBC, MySQL, JavaFX for UI.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="project">
            <h3>3. Online Banking System</h3>
            <p><strong>Description:</strong> Designed a banking application to manage customer accounts, transactions, and fund transfers.</p>
            <p><strong>Features:</strong> Account creation, balance inquiry, deposit/withdrawal, and secure login.</p>
            <p><strong>Technologies Used:</strong> Java, Spring MVC, Hibernate, MySQL, JSP.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="project">
            <h3>4. Library Management System</h3>
            <p><strong>Description:</strong> Built a software solution for libraries to manage book inventories and member records.</p>
            <p><strong>Features:</strong> Book lending/return, member registration, and fine calculation.</p>
            <p><strong>Technologies Used:</strong> Java, Swing, JDBC, MySQL.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="project">
            <h3>5. Weather Forecast Application</h3>
            <p><strong>Description:</strong> Created an application that provides real-time weather updates using a public API.</p>
            <p><strong>Features:</strong> City-based weather search, temperature, and forecast details.</p>
            <p><strong>Technologies Used:</strong> Java, REST APIs, JSON, JavaFX.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2025 Java Developer Portfolio</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
